WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:09.718 --> 00:00:11.761 position:50% align:center
[BOY 79A] You guys
aren't foolin' anybody!

00:00:11.845 --> 00:00:12.846 position:50% align:center
We're better than you

00:00:12.929 --> 00:00:15.056 position:50% align:center
and we'll take you
down to prove it!

00:00:15.140 --> 00:00:17.600 position:50% align:center
Oh? Then bring it on.

00:00:17.684 --> 00:00:19.811 position:50% align:center
Let's have a proper fight.

00:00:22.939 --> 00:00:25.275 position:50% align:center
My Binging Balls'll
make a feast outta you.

00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:26.901 position:50% align:center
Bet you didn't see that coming!

00:00:26.985 --> 00:00:29.904 position:50% align:center
These monsters are
super fast and strong.

00:00:32.490 --> 00:00:33.908 position:50% align:center
[BOY 79E]
Assault Dust!

00:00:33.992 --> 00:00:35.744 position:50% align:center
Those guys aren't gonna
know what hit 'em!

00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:37.328 position:50% align:center
C'mon, let's go!

00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:38.997 position:50% align:center
[YOARASHI grunting]

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:40.498 position:50% align:center
A dust cloud.

00:00:40.582 --> 00:00:42.751 position:50% align:center
Viral Cosmos!

00:00:42.834 --> 00:00:44.627 position:50% align:center
Electromagnetic Bullets!

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:46.463 position:50% align:center
And King Slam!

00:00:46.546 --> 00:00:48.173 position:50% align:center
Hula Hoop attack!

00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:50.091 position:50% align:center
Go Tongue Tank!

00:02:23.852 --> 00:02:26.354 position:50% align:center
[rumbling]

00:02:26.438 --> 00:02:32.485 position:50% align:center
Uh, what? Kids these
days are stupid strong!

00:02:32.569 --> 00:02:34.571 position:50% align:center
How is this even possible, huh?

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:35.822 position:50% align:center
Back when I was their age,

00:02:35.905 --> 00:02:38.450 position:50% align:center
I was just learning how
to get my yell working.

00:02:38.533 --> 00:02:39.617 position:50% align:center
Having this much power

00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:42.328 position:50% align:center
when you're just a tyke
should be illegal.

00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:44.164 position:50% align:center
[SHISHIKURA]
Allow me to explain.

00:02:44.247 --> 00:02:45.874 position:50% align:center
As the generations pass,

00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.877 position:50% align:center
Quirks combine and
become more powerful.

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:51.588 position:50% align:center
Hypothetically, stronger,
more complex Quirks

00:02:51.671 --> 00:02:54.382 position:50% align:center
may one day become too hard
for anyone to control,

00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:57.719 position:50% align:center
especially untrained children.

00:02:57.802 --> 00:02:59.721 position:50% align:center
Quirk singularity doomsday.

00:02:59.804 --> 00:03:02.599 position:50% align:center
That's what they
call this theory.

00:03:02.682 --> 00:03:06.353 position:50% align:center
These kids make me fearful
that this is indeed our future.

00:03:06.436 --> 00:03:10.315 position:50% align:center
[IKOMA gasps] I'm sorry! Please
forgive me! It's all my fault.

00:03:10.398 --> 00:03:12.942 position:50% align:center
[PRESENT MIC]
Wait, don't leave now!

00:03:13.026 --> 00:03:16.196 position:50% align:center
Stay. This jam is
just gettin' started.

00:03:16.279 --> 00:03:18.615 position:50% align:center
Let's see how they react.

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:20.992 position:50% align:center
Gang Orca. Is this okay?

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:24.621 position:50% align:center
[GANG ORCA]
Okay? Why would you ask?!

00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:26.748 position:50% align:center
Do you think I'm not
paying attention?

00:03:26.831 --> 00:03:28.958 position:50% align:center
That this was unexpected
and not the outcome

00:03:29.042 --> 00:03:30.418 position:50% align:center
I planned for from
the very beginning?

00:03:30.502 --> 00:03:34.047 position:50% align:center
[TRAINEES] No, sir!
Of course not! We're sorry!

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:36.800 position:50% align:center
[GANG ORCA]
These are aspiring young heroes.

00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:39.719 position:50% align:center
[GANG ORCA]
They may be failures,

00:03:39.803 --> 00:03:42.055 position:50% align:center
but they can handle themselves.

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:49.938 position:50% align:center
Pretty bold of them to attack

00:03:50.021 --> 00:03:53.817 position:50% align:center
without hesitation like that.
I'm almost impressed.

00:03:53.900 --> 00:03:55.735 position:50% align:center
They know that
we're hero trainees.

00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:58.863 position:50% align:center
They likely feel they don't
need to hold back against us.

00:03:58.947 --> 00:04:01.449 position:50% align:center
It's so sad! I wanna
be their friend.

00:04:01.533 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center
Even if it wasn't
part of our training.

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:05.954 position:50% align:center
[BOY 79A]
No way!

00:04:06.037 --> 00:04:08.415 position:50% align:center
They're not scared of our
Quirks at all? Seriously?

00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:09.791 position:50% align:center
[KID LEADER] They think
they're better than us

00:04:09.874 --> 00:04:11.209 position:50% align:center
just because they're older.

00:04:11.292 --> 00:04:12.544 position:50% align:center
Come on, everyone.

00:04:12.627 --> 00:04:14.337 position:50% align:center
Let's show 'em more
of what we got.

00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:18.341 position:50% align:center
Leave it up to me!
Queen Beam, shoot!

00:04:20.343 --> 00:04:22.262 position:50% align:center
[TODOROKI]
Hey.

00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:25.098 position:50% align:center
Wow. You've got such
a beautiful face, dear.

00:04:25.181 --> 00:04:27.434 position:50% align:center
Don't let that frown
spoil the effect.

00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:29.144 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:32.439 --> 00:04:36.151 position:50% align:center
Sorry, hon, just a
little illusion for ya.

00:04:38.028 --> 00:04:40.071 position:50% align:center
Wouldn't it be, like,
so swoony though?

00:04:40.155 --> 00:04:41.489 position:50% align:center
Our school's mega old-fashioned

00:04:41.573 --> 00:04:43.491 position:50% align:center
and doesn't even allow
us to go on dates.

00:04:43.575 --> 00:04:45.243 position:50% align:center
Ugh, it's just the worst.

00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:46.870 position:50% align:center
[PRESENT MIC] Shiketsu
High School second year,

00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:48.163 position:50% align:center
Camie Utsushimi.

00:04:48.246 --> 00:04:49.581 position:50% align:center
Her Quirk: Glamour.

00:04:49.664 --> 00:04:52.000 position:50% align:center
She can create illusions
for a short period of time.

00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:54.419 position:50% align:center
Abuse of this Quirk
is prohibited!

00:04:54.502 --> 00:04:55.962 position:50% align:center
[KATSUKI muffled laughter]

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:58.840 position:50% align:center
"You've got such a
beautiful face, my dear."

00:04:58.923 --> 00:05:00.342 position:50% align:center
[KATSUKI]
That killed me, Glamouroki!

00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:01.885 position:50% align:center
Seriously, I might die.

00:05:01.968 --> 00:05:05.013 position:50% align:center
Oh? I dunno, was it
really all that funny?

00:05:05.096 --> 00:05:06.473 position:50% align:center
Anyway!

00:05:06.556 --> 00:05:08.350 position:50% align:center
Let's do the thing we were
talking about before, guys!

00:05:08.433 --> 00:05:11.269 position:50% align:center
[KID LEADER] You idiots
think you know so much!

00:05:11.353 --> 00:05:13.480 position:50% align:center
But I outshine adults
at everything!

00:05:13.563 --> 00:05:18.026 position:50% align:center
Piano, fighting: it doesn't
matter! I'm a prodigy!

00:05:18.109 --> 00:05:19.569 position:50% align:center
I see the heroes
who get in trouble

00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:22.572 position:50% align:center
every day on TV! And the police!

00:05:22.655 --> 00:05:24.574 position:50% align:center
Then there's our weepy teacher.

00:05:24.657 --> 00:05:27.202 position:50% align:center
You're all completely
hopeless compared to me!

00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:29.871 position:50% align:center
To us! We'll show you
that we can use our powers

00:05:29.954 --> 00:05:31.664 position:50% align:center
better than you
ever even imagined!

00:05:31.748 --> 00:05:33.291 position:50% align:center
Just watch!

00:05:33.375 --> 00:05:34.209 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:34.292 --> 00:05:38.630 position:50% align:center
[KIDS yelling]

00:05:40.090 --> 00:05:42.592 position:50% align:center
You kids are amazing,
I'll give ya that.

00:05:42.676 --> 00:05:46.471 position:50% align:center
Thing is, there's more
to heroing than just power!

00:05:46.554 --> 00:05:47.972 position:50% align:center
Here I go!

00:05:48.056 --> 00:05:49.182 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.393 position:50% align:center
It's so lame that we
can't do this outside.

00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:52.977 position:50% align:center
Ugh, whatevs.

00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:58.775 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:07.742 position:50% align:center
[BOY 79A yelps]

00:06:16.793 --> 00:06:18.920 position:50% align:center
[grunting]

00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:20.880 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.636 position:50% align:center
Ah!

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:27.721 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:06:27.804 --> 00:06:30.140 position:50% align:center
[GIRL 79D]
Amazing!

00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:31.141 position:50% align:center
--[gasps]
--[PRESENT MIC whistles]

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:37.105 position:50% align:center
[KIDS laughing, chattering]

00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:38.565 position:50% align:center
Whoa, what?

00:06:38.648 --> 00:06:40.608 position:50% align:center
I didn't know these
guys could do this!

00:06:40.692 --> 00:06:42.777 position:50% align:center
What the heck did
they do to this place?

00:06:42.861 --> 00:06:44.529 position:50% align:center
I'm loving it.

00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:47.741 position:50% align:center
I can't make complex
structures out of my ice yet,

00:06:47.824 --> 00:06:51.411 position:50% align:center
so I used the objects you made
as a frame for my design.

00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:55.206 position:50% align:center
Fortunately you have
some amazing powers.

00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:57.834 position:50% align:center
[BOY 79G] Hey, I wanna
do it, too! No fair!

00:06:57.917 --> 00:06:59.169 position:50% align:center
[GIRL 79A]
I wanna try the slide!

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:00.628 position:50% align:center
--[BOY 79D] Me next...
--[TODOROKI] Sure. Line up.

00:07:00.712 --> 00:07:03.173 position:50% align:center
[KIDS laughing, clamoring]

00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:04.758 position:50% align:center
[KATSUKI] All we gotta do
is show these brats

00:07:04.841 --> 00:07:07.218 position:50% align:center
how impressive we are.

00:07:07.302 --> 00:07:08.678 position:50% align:center
'Cause, c'mon.

00:07:08.762 --> 00:07:10.889 position:50% align:center
Lose to someone you look
down on and you feel like crap.

00:07:10.972 --> 00:07:13.725 position:50% align:center
That's not the way we're gonna
win their hearts or whatever.

00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:16.686 position:50% align:center
We have to set them
on the right path.

00:07:18.813 --> 00:07:21.191 position:50% align:center
Otherwise they'll end up
causing problems later on.

00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:23.860 position:50% align:center
The same way I did during
the provisional exam.

00:07:23.943 --> 00:07:27.364 position:50% align:center
I don't want them to go
down that same path!

00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:28.865 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:07:28.948 --> 00:07:32.118 position:50% align:center
If we can't broaden their
horizons, then what's the point?

00:07:32.202 --> 00:07:34.621 position:50% align:center
We'd make bad heroes.

00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:38.333 position:50% align:center
Playing instead of attacking.

00:07:38.416 --> 00:07:40.126 position:50% align:center
In order to create
a bond between them

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:41.920 position:50% align:center
without breaking
anyone's spirit.

00:07:42.003 --> 00:07:44.172 position:50% align:center
Rockin' use of your
Quirks, you guys.

00:07:44.255 --> 00:07:46.383 position:50% align:center
I was startin' to sweat.

00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:49.302 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:49.386 --> 00:07:52.931 position:50% align:center
You, too. Get in there
and have some fun.

00:07:53.014 --> 00:07:55.600 position:50% align:center
What are you doing?
Get your hands off of me!

00:07:55.684 --> 00:07:56.976 position:50% align:center
You think I'm impressed by this?

00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:58.603 position:50% align:center
You're their leader,
aren't you, kid?

00:07:58.687 --> 00:07:59.854 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:59.938 --> 00:08:02.399 position:50% align:center
If you keep looking
down on everyone else,

00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:05.026 position:50% align:center
you'll never be able to
see your own weaknesses.

00:08:06.945 --> 00:08:09.406 position:50% align:center
That's just some advice
from one of your elders,

00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:12.200 position:50% align:center
so don't forget it. Ugh.

00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:13.868 position:50% align:center
Hey, Baldy! Todoroki!

00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:15.495 position:50% align:center
I'm not bald.

00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:19.958 position:50% align:center
[KID LEADER]
What he said just now...

00:08:20.041 --> 00:08:22.085 position:50% align:center
He wasn't talking down to me.

00:08:22.168 --> 00:08:25.255 position:50% align:center
But... did he really
mean all that?

00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:28.174 position:50% align:center
Yes. I think he did.

00:08:28.258 --> 00:08:32.303 position:50% align:center
His words... I can feel
how true they are.

00:08:32.387 --> 00:08:33.805 position:50% align:center
Next, let's all work together.

00:08:33.888 --> 00:08:35.598 position:50% align:center
We'll make something
even more amazing!

00:08:35.682 --> 00:08:37.976 position:50% align:center
How about an exploding
roller coaster?!

00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:39.477 position:50% align:center
[BOYS]
Yeah!

00:08:39.561 --> 00:08:41.646 position:50% align:center
[TODOROKI]
That's not gonna happen.

00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:45.734 position:50% align:center
[IKOMA] My problem children.
What's going on here?

00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:48.778 position:50% align:center
[PRESENT MIC] After this,
it's your turn, ma'am.

00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:52.532 position:50% align:center
Make sure you keep
this vibe goin'.

00:08:52.615 --> 00:08:53.992 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:08:55.618 --> 00:08:58.830 position:50% align:center
Why is it so important
to be the strongest?

00:09:00.331 --> 00:09:02.208 position:50% align:center
[ALL MIGHT]
Tell me, Endeavor.

00:09:02.292 --> 00:09:06.296 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you have a
reason. So what is it?

00:09:09.299 --> 00:09:11.009 position:50% align:center
[GANG ORCA] "Work together
and win the hearts

00:09:11.092 --> 00:09:13.261 position:50% align:center
of those children."

00:09:13.345 --> 00:09:15.013 position:50% align:center
You did a good job
despite having

00:09:15.096 --> 00:09:16.765 position:50% align:center
such vague instructions.

00:09:16.848 --> 00:09:19.351 position:50% align:center
[KATSUKI, YOARASHI] Wait,
so you did that on purpose?

00:09:19.434 --> 00:09:21.978 position:50% align:center
[GANG ORCA]
The rest of you also did well.

00:09:22.062 --> 00:09:24.230 position:50% align:center
Remember everything
you learned today.

00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:25.565 position:50% align:center
And keep working.

00:09:25.648 --> 00:09:28.985 position:50% align:center
You students have so
much potential--uh...

00:09:29.069 --> 00:09:30.695 position:50% align:center
I mean, don't you dare fail!

00:09:30.779 --> 00:09:32.322 position:50% align:center
[TRAINEES]
Sir, yes, sir!

00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:34.824 position:50% align:center
He's actually a big
softy who loves kids.

00:09:34.908 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
This is just for show.

00:09:39.454 --> 00:09:40.997 position:50% align:center
After what we put
together in there,

00:09:41.081 --> 00:09:43.249 position:50% align:center
I think we're meant
to be friends, don't you?

00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:45.335 position:50% align:center
Our Quirks just work
so well together.

00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:46.503 position:50% align:center
You think so?

00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:48.588 position:50% align:center
Yeah, and Bakugo,
you're actually not bad

00:09:48.672 --> 00:09:50.590 position:50% align:center
if you don't talk.
Try shutting up!

00:09:50.674 --> 00:09:53.009 position:50% align:center
You shut up!

00:09:53.093 --> 00:09:54.260 position:50% align:center
[ALL MIGHT]
Sounds good.

00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:55.095 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:55.178 --> 00:09:56.304 position:50% align:center
[YOARASHI gasps]

00:09:56.388 --> 00:09:58.390 position:50% align:center
We'll also do whatever
we can to help you.

00:09:58.473 --> 00:10:00.600 position:50% align:center
[CAMIE] Ooh, what's
going on, Shishikura?

00:10:00.684 --> 00:10:02.268 position:50% align:center
You schmoozing with All Might?

00:10:02.352 --> 00:10:04.813 position:50% align:center
Seriously, the Symbol?
What were you talking about?

00:10:04.896 --> 00:10:06.231 position:50% align:center
Like, Hero stuff or what?

00:10:06.314 --> 00:10:08.483 position:50% align:center
We were talking about you. Fool!

00:10:08.566 --> 00:10:10.443 position:50% align:center
For realzies? That's sweet.

00:10:10.527 --> 00:10:12.404 position:50% align:center
The reality is that,
by attacking you,

00:10:12.487 --> 00:10:15.073 position:50% align:center
the League went after
a school other than UA.

00:10:15.156 --> 00:10:16.908 position:50% align:center
Up until now,
our schools haven't

00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:19.994 position:50% align:center
had an especially close
relationship with each other.

00:10:20.078 --> 00:10:22.247 position:50% align:center
But we were talking about
coordinating in the future

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:25.208 position:50% align:center
for the sake of
sharing information.

00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:28.211 position:50% align:center
We still don't know why you
were targeted, Miss Utsushimi.

00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
But hopefully, together,
we'll get a better idea

00:10:30.380 --> 00:10:31.673 position:50% align:center
of what the villains want.

00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:32.757 position:50% align:center
Cray-cray.

00:10:32.841 --> 00:10:34.634 position:50% align:center
Additionally, this means
we can organize

00:10:34.718 --> 00:10:36.594 position:50% align:center
joint training
exercises someday.

00:10:36.678 --> 00:10:38.722 position:50% align:center
[KATSUKI] Next time,
I'll beat you up one-on-one.

00:10:38.805 --> 00:10:39.931 position:50% align:center
You still behave and speak

00:10:40.015 --> 00:10:41.808 position:50% align:center
like a back-alley
thug, you hoodlum!

00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:43.351 position:50% align:center
Remember your place!

00:10:43.435 --> 00:10:46.479 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you don't get to be
the one to tell me that.

00:10:46.563 --> 00:10:50.191 position:50% align:center
[ENDEAVOR]
Shoto. Long time no see.

00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:51.568 position:50% align:center
You've changed quite a bit.

00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:53.319 position:50% align:center
Not interested.

00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:57.532 position:50% align:center
[ENDEAVOR]
Shoto...

00:11:01.786 --> 00:11:04.622 position:50% align:center
I want you to know
I'm proud of you, son.

00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:08.084 position:50% align:center
[ENDEAVOR]
Because of that,

00:11:08.168 --> 00:11:12.672 position:50% align:center
I swear I'll become someone
you can be proud of, too.

00:11:12.756 --> 00:11:15.592 position:50% align:center
Not just as the number-one hero,

00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:18.720 position:50% align:center
but as the man that
you call father.

